criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Type 1 diabetes mellitus;

          2. Age≥12 yr;

          3. Tanner sexual maturation rating 2-5;

          4. HbA1c levels: 7.5%-10%;

          5. MDI or CSII ≥6 months;

          6. Insulin dose ≥ 0.8U/kg before the enrollment，and the dosage is stable at least ＞1
             month（dosage change<10%）.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Serious acute and chronic complications associated with diabetes;

          2. Repeated and serious hypoglycemia episodes repeatedly;

          3. Hepatic function damage (ALT≥2.5 times higher than the upper limit of the normal
             accepted range);

          4. Moderate to advanced renal impairment (calculated according to MDRD equation:
             eGFR<60ml/min/1.73m2);

          5. Clinically significant heart attacks: myocardial infarction,
             arrhythmia，II-III°AVB，unstable angina，decompensated HF（NYHA III~IV;

          6. Female patients who have a sex life and are not willing to use contraceptive methods;

          7. Pregnancy.
